About Me

Hello I am Alex Funk. A Fourth year Computer Science major, Philosophy minor and Technology Management Certificate pursuer. I love to paint, surf, spend time with my friends and play videogames. I also have been building a company for the last ten months and am excited for what the future may hold. I will be working at Apeel Sciences this summer and could not be more excited. Feel free to take a look around this place. You'll find my paintings and other goodies I find interesting and enjoy.

Background at UCSB

I came into UCSB as a computer science major, so I've taken all the lower-division computer science courses required of the major. I've also taken a handful of upper-division CS courses during my time here. Some of the upper division classes that I took last quarter are:

  • CS 130B
  • CS 154
  • CS 178
